The shared-burden principle and the Charter of Passage's absolute access-right share a philosophical premise: essential resources are community obligations, not individual privileges.
Rakuen's experience of annexation-era resource constraints gave Water Court history particular relevance — understanding how the Court maintained equitable distribution during crises informed Garden Ledger design.

